---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CtaSection from '../components/CtaSection.astro';
import stackedLogo from '../assets/HoundStackTextwLogo-trim.svg';
import { SITE } from '../lib/site';

const personSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Person',
  name: 'Brendan Schmidt',
  jobTitle: 'Founder',
  url: new URL('/about', SITE.url).href,
  worksFor: {
    '@type': 'Organization',
    name: 'HoundStack',
    url: SITE.url,
  },
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About HoundStack"
  description="Why founder Brendan Schmidt built HoundStack: software for the people who show up every day to take care of dogs, after watching this trade run on tools that charge for every user and were built for other work."
  schema={[personSchema]}
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <span class="eyebrow">About</span>
      <h1>Built for the people who show up for dogs</h1>

      <div class="about-body">
        <p class="lede">
          HoundStack exists to make life easier for the people who show up every day to take care
          of dogs. That means the crews running the routes, and it also means the dogs waiting on
          a clean yard.
        </p>
        <p>
          It started with looking closely at how pet waste removal businesses actually run their
          day to day. What we found was a trade whose software had not caught up with it. Tools
          charging for every user from the very first one, so the first hire means a bigger
          software bill. Pet waste features bolted onto platforms built for a dozen other trades,
          so per dog pricing, rain day billing, and gate codes all live in workarounds.
        </p>
        <p>
          So HoundStack is built from the route up for this trade alone. Pricing stays
          predictable: your first teammates are included, and each one after is a flat $10 a
          month. The billing understands why a visit was skipped. The field app assumes a truck,
          a gate, and sometimes no signal. None of that is adaptation. It is the starting point.
        </p>
        <p>
          If that sounds like software made by people who paid attention, that is the whole
          intent. See <a href="/features">what it does</a>, check <a href="/pricing">what it costs</a>, or <a href="/contact">talk to us</a> directly.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="founder-card">
        <h2>Who is building it</h2>
        <p>
          HoundStack is built by <strong>Brendan Schmidt</strong>, its founder. The paragraphs
          above are his reasons, not a marketing team's: he went looking at how scooper businesses
          actually run a Tuesday, decided the software this trade was renting did not deserve it,
          and started building the one it should have had.
        </p>
        <p>
          It is early, and that is on purpose too. If you run routes and something in the product
          fights you, <a href="/contact">tell him directly</a> — that feedback is currently the
          product roadmap.
        </p>
        <p class="founder-sig">Brendan Schmidt · Founder, HoundStack</p>
      </div>

      <img
        src={stackedLogo.src}
        alt="HoundStack logo, a faceted geometric mark above the wordmark"
        width="280"
        height="180"
        class="about-logo"
        loading="lazy"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <CtaSection />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    padding-top: clamp(40px, 6vw, 72px);
    padding-bottom: clamp(48px, 6vw, 80px);
  }

  .about-body {
    max-width: 640px;
  }

  .founder-card {
    max-width: 640px;
    margin-top: 40px;
    padding: 28px;
    background: var(--bg-alt);
    border: 1px solid var(--line-soft);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
  }

  .founder-card h2 {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
  }

  .founder-sig {
    margin: 0;
    font-weight: 650;
    color: var(--navy);
  }

  /* Centered sign-off mark under the founder card, not an orphaned
     image floating at the content edge. */
  .about-logo {
    display: block;
    margin: 56px auto 0;
    width: 170px;
    height: auto;
    opacity: 0.9;
  }
</style>
